    {
        "content": "<p>Where would I place <code>import Mathlib.Tactic</code> to make it available project-wide, instead of at the top of every file?</p>",
        "id": 498482231,
        "sender_full_name": "spamegg",
        "timestamp": 1739003556
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>That can't be done. But note that imports are transitive so if you <code>import Mathlib.Tactic</code> on <code>A.lean</code> and <code>B.lean</code> imports <code>A</code> then <code>B</code> will have <code>Mathlib.Tactic</code> available</p>",
        "id": 498485785,
        "sender_full_name": "Arthur Paulino",
        "timestamp": 1739006808
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>So I could place all commonly reused imports into a file, say <code>Common.lean</code> then <code>import Common</code> in other files.</p>",
        "id": 498485840,
        "sender_full_name": "spamegg",
        "timestamp": 1739006875
